premise_source_doc_sentence: Central Pashto  (  منځنۍ پښتو manźanəi pax̌to  )  is the standardized variety of Pashto which serves as a prestige Pashto dialect , and is based on the Ghilji dialect , spoken in the central Ghilji region , which covers the eastern Afghan region of Paktika , northern Zabul , southern Ghazni , Kabul  (  including Afghan capital Kabul  )  and some surrounding region .
